The paper deals with the construction of linear codes and their weight enumerators, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT) and coding theory (cs.CR). The use of defining sets and the absolute trace function suggests a connection to algebraic geometry and algebraic coding theory, which are also relevant to discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The applications of the codes in association schemes and secret sharing schemes suggest a connection to cryptography (cs.CR) and security and privacy (cs.SI). Overall, cs.IT and cs.CR are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.DM, cs.CC, and cs.SI.
